Reasoning: The paper discusses a comparative study of blockchain technologies, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves the disentanglement of blockchains into building blocks and their hierarchical classification, which relates to distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The identification and comparison of alternative layouts for the subcomponents of blockchains also involves database systems (cs.DB) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
